  "title": "Lesson 12: Identities Involving Square Roots",
  "slug": "lesson_12_identities_involving_square_roots",
  "content": "<div class=\"pt-6 font-sans\">\n    <!-- Lesson Title and Introduction -->\n    <div class=\"text-center px-4\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-800\">Lesson 12: Identities Involving Square Roots</h1>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-lg text-sky-600 font-medium\">The Rules of the Game!</p>\n        <p class=\"mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed\">\n            Working with expressions like (√5 + √7) can look intimidating. But what if they follow a set of simple, predictable rules, just like the algebraic identities you already know? Let's learn these powerful shortcuts to simplify complex-looking expressions with ease.\n        </p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Hooking Illustration -->\n    <div class=\"flex justify-center my-8 px-4\">\n        <svg viewBox=\"0 0 500 200\" class=\"w-full max-w-lg\">\n           <rect x=\"20\" y=\"50\" width=\"200\" height=\"100\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" rx=\"10\"/>\n           <text x=\"120\" y=\"105\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"20\" text-anchor=\"middle\">(a + b)²</text>\n\n           <rect x=\"280\" y=\"50\" width=\"200\" height=\"100\" fill=\"#fee2e2\" rx=\"10\"/>\n           <text x=\"380\" y=\"105\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"20\" text-anchor=\"middle\">(√a + √b)²</text>\n\n           <path d=\"M225 100 H 275\" stroke=\"#4b5563\" stroke-width=\"3\"/>\n           <polygon points=\"275,92 285,100 275,108\" fill=\"#4b5563\"/>\n           \n           <text x=\"250\" y=\"30\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">If you know the rule for this...</text>\n           <text x=\"250\" y=\"180\" font-size=\"18\" fill=\"#374151\" text-anchor=\"middle\">...then you already know the rule for this!</text>\n        </svg>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Section 1: The Basic Identities -->\n    <div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4\">1. The Two Foundational Rules</h2>\n        <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6\">\n            Almost everything we do with square roots comes from two very basic and intuitive identities. These are our primary tools.\n        </p>\n        <div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\">\n            <!-- Identity 1 -->\n            <div class=\"bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6\">\n                <h3 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-2 text-center\">Identity 1: √(ab) = √a × √b</h3>\n                 <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-4\">The square root of a product is the product of the square roots.</p>\n                <div class=\"p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm\">\n                    <p class=\"font-mono text-lg text-gray-800\"><strong>Example: Simplify √12</strong></p>\n                    <p class=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">We can write 12 as 4 × 3.</p>\n                    <p class=\"text-lg font-mono text-green-600 mt-2\">√12 = √(4 × 3) = √4 × √3 = 2√3</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <!-- Identity 2 -->\n            <div class=\"bg-sky-50 rounded-xl p-6\">\n                 <h3 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-sky-800 mb-2 text-center\">Identity 2: √(a/b) = √a / √b</h3>\n                 <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-4\">The square root of a fraction is the fraction of the square roots.</p>\n                <div class=\"p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm\">\n                    <p class=\"font-mono text-lg text-gray-800\"><strong>Example: Simplify √(9/25)</strong></p>\n                    <p class=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">We take the square root of the top and bottom separately.</p>\n                    <p class=\"text-lg font-mono text-sky-600 mt-2\">√(9/25) = √9 / √25 = 3/5</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Section 2: Extending Algebraic Identities -->\n    <div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4\">2. Using Your Algebra Skills</h2>\n        <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6\">\n            The familiar algebraic identities you learned for variables like 'x' and 'y' apply perfectly to square roots. This makes simplifying complex expressions much easier.\n        </p>\n        \n        <!-- Identity 3: Difference of Squares -->\n        <div class=\"bg-amber-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-amber-800 mb-2\">Identity 3: (√a + √b)(√a - √b) = a - b</h3>\n            <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg\">This is just like (x+y)(x-y) = x² - y². Here, (√a)² = a and (√b)² = b.</p>\n            <h4 class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\">Example: Simplify (√7 + √3)(√7 - √3)</h4>\n            <div class=\"p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm font-mono mt-2\">\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= (√7)² - (√3)²</p>\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= 7 - 3</p>\n                <p class=\"text-xl font-bold text-amber-700\">= 4</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        \n        <!-- Identity 4: Squaring a Binomial -->\n        <div class=\"bg-violet-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-violet-800 mb-2\">Identity 4: (√a + √b)² = a + 2√(ab) + b</h3>\n            <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg\">This is just like (x+y)² = x² + 2xy + y². Here, x² is a, y² is b, and 2xy is 2√a√b = 2√(ab).</p>\n            <h4 class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\">Example: Simplify (√5 + √2)²</h4>\n            <div class=\"p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm font-mono mt-2\">\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= (√5)² + 2(√5)(√2) + (√2)²</p>\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= 5 + 2√(5×2) + 2</p>\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= 5 + 2√10 + 2</p>\n                <p class=\"text-xl font-bold text-violet-700\">= 7 + 2√10</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <!-- Identity 5: Standard Multiplication -->\n         <div class=\"bg-red-50 rounded-xl p-6\">\n            <h3 class=\"text-2xl font-bold text-red-800 mb-2\">Identity 5: (√a + √b)(√c + √d)</h3>\n            <p class=\"text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg\">This is just like standard binomial multiplication (FOIL method). Multiply each term in the first bracket by each term in the second.</p>\n            <h4 class=\"font-semibold text-gray-800\">Example: Simplify (√2 + √3)(√5 + √7)</h4>\n            <div class=\"p-4 bg-white rounded-lg shadow-sm font-mono mt-2\">\n                <p class=\"text-gray-700 text-lg\">= (√2 × √5) + (√2 × √7) + (√3 × √5) + (√3 × √7)</p>\n                <p class=\"text-xl font-bold text-red-700\">= √10 + √14 + √15 + √21</p>\n                <p class=\"text-sm italic text-gray-500 font-sans mt-2\">(Since none of the roots are like terms, this cannot be simplified further.)</p>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Summary Section -->\n    <div class=\"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12\">\n        <h2 class=\"text-3xl font-bold text-center text-gray-800 mb-8\">Lesson 12 Summary</h2>\n        <div class=\"bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-6\">\n             <div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 items-center\">\n                <div class=\"flex justify-center\">\n                   <svg viewBox=\"0 0 300 250\" class=\"w-full max-w-sm\">\n                        <rect x=\"10\" y=\"20\" width=\"280\" height=\"210\" rx=\"15\" fill=\"#e0f2fe\" stroke=\"#0ea5e9\" stroke-width=\"2\"/>\n                        <text x=\"150\" y=\"50\" font-size=\"20\" font-weight=\"bold\" text-anchor=\"middle\">Key Identities</text>\n                        <text x=\"30\" y=\"90\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"16\">√(ab) = √a × √b</text>\n                        <text x=\"30\" y=\"120\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"16\">(√a+√b)(√a-√b) = a-b</text>\n                        <text x=\"30\" y=\"150\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"16\">(√a+√b)² = a+2√ab+b</text>\n                        <text x=\"30\" y=\"180\" font-family=\"monospace\" font-size=\"16\">(a+√b)(a-√b) = a²-b</text>\n                    </svg>\n                </div>\n                <div class=\"text-gray-700 space-y-4\">\n                    <p>✔️ Operations with square roots follow the same logic as operations with algebraic variables.</p>\n                    <p>✔️ The key is to recognize which identity pattern an expression matches.</p>\n                    <p>✔️ The \"Difference of Squares\" identity, (a+b)(a-b) = a²-b², is especially useful for removing square roots from an expression.</p>\n                    <p>✔️ These identities are the essential shortcuts for simplifying complex expressions and will be crucial for our next lesson.</p>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
  "questions": "<div class=\"pt-6 font-sans\">\n    <!-- Lesson Title -->\n    <div class=\"text-center px-4 mb-12\">\n        <h1 class=\"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-800\">Lesson 12: Check Your Understanding</h1>\n        <p class=\"mt-2 text-lg text-sky-600 font-medium\">Test your skills with square root identities!</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Question 1 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 1: The Difference of Squares</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Simplify the expression:   <strong>(√11 - √7)(√11 + √7)</strong></p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Recognize the pattern. This expression matches the identity (a - b)(a + b) = a² - b², where a = √11 and b = √7.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Apply the identity: (√11)² - (√7)².</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> The square and the square root cancel each other out.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">11 - 7</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 4</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Question 2 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 2: Squaring a Binomial</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Simplify the expression:   <strong>(√3 + √5)²</strong></p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Recognize the pattern. This matches the identity (a + b)² = a² + 2ab + b², where a = √3 and b = √5.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Apply the identity: (√3)² + 2(√3)(√5) + (√5)².</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Simplify each term.</p>\n                 <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2\">\n                    <li>(√3)² = 3</li>\n                    <li>2(√3)(√5) = 2√(3×5) = 2√15</li>\n                    <li>(√5)² = 5</li>\n                </ul>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Combine the rational terms (3 and 5).</p>\n                 <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">3 + 5 + 2√15</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 8 + 2√15</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Question 3 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 3: Standard Multiplication (FOIL)</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Simplify the expression:   <strong>(5 + √7)(2 + √5)</strong></p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">We need to multiply each term in the first bracket by each term in the second (First, Outer, Inner, Last).</p>\n                <div class=\"flex justify-center my-4\">\n                    <svg viewBox=\"0 0 500 150\" class=\"w-full max-w-lg\">\n                        <text x=\"150\" y=\"80\" font-size=\"20\" font-family=\"monospace\" text-anchor=\"middle\">(5 + √7)(2 + √5)</text>\n                        <path d=\"M70 65 C 100 30, 180 30, 210 65\" stroke=\"#ef4444\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                        <text x=\"140\" y=\"25\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#ef4444\">First: 5 × 2 = 10</text>\n                        <path d=\"M70 85 C 150 140, 260 140, 310 85\" stroke=\"#3b82f6\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                        <text x=\"190\" y=\"155\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#3b82f6\">Outer: 5 × √5 = 5√5</text>\n                        <path d=\"M140 85 C 160 110, 190 110, 210 85\" stroke=\"#16a34a\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                        <text x=\"175\" y=\"125\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#16a34a\">Inner: √7 × 2 = 2√7</text>\n                        <path d=\"M140 65 C 200 10, 280 10, 310 65\" stroke=\"#d97706\" fill=\"none\"/>\n                        <text x=\"225\" y=\"5\" font-size=\"12\" fill=\"#d97706\">Last: √7 × √5 = √35</text>\n                    </svg>\n                </div>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">Now, add all the results together: 10 + 5√5 + 2√7 + √35.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">Since there are no like terms, we cannot simplify this any further.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 10 + 5√5 + 2√7 + √35</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Question 4 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 4: Mixed Difference of Squares</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Simplify the expression:   <strong>(5 + √3)(5 - √3)</strong></p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> This also matches the identity (a + b)(a - b) = a² - b², but this time a = 5 and b = √3.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Apply the identity: (5)² - (√3)².</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Simplify each term.</p>\n                 <ul class=\"list-disc list-inside ml-4 space-y-2\">\n                    <li>(5)² = 25</li>\n                    <li>(√3)² = 3</li>\n                </ul>\n                <p class=\"mb-2 mt-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Calculate the final result.</p>\n                <p class=\"font-mono text-lg ml-6 mt-1 text-gray-700\">25 - 3</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 22</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <!-- Question 5 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 5: A Basic Identity</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Using an identity, simplify <strong>√2 × √18</strong>.</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 1:</strong> Use the identity √a × √b = √(a × b).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 2:</strong> Apply this to our problem: √2 × √18 = √(2 × 18).</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 3:</strong> Calculate the product inside the square root: 2 × 18 = 36.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\"><strong>Step 4:</strong> Our expression is now √36. We can simplify this because 36 is a perfect square.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: 6</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <!-- Question 6 -->\n    <div class=\"question-answer-container max-w-4xl mx-auto p-4 mb-8\">\n        <h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4\">Question 6: Which Identity to Use?</h3>\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-gray-700\">Which algebraic identity is most useful for simplifying the expression <strong>(√6 - √2)²</strong>?</p>\n        <button class=\"show-answer-button mt-4 bg-sky-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-sky-600 transition duration-300\">Show Answer</button>\n        <div class=\"answer-container mt-4 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg\">\n            <h4 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-700 mb-2\">Answer Breakdown:</h4>\n            <div class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed\">\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">The expression is a binomial (two terms) that is being squared. Specifically, it is a difference that is being squared.</p>\n                <p class=\"mb-2\">This matches the pattern of the \"square of a difference\" identity.</p>\n            </div>\n            <p class=\"mt-4 font-bold text-lg text-green-600\">Final Answer: The identity <strong>(a - b)² = a² - 2ab + b²</strong>.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n</div>\n<!--end-of-code-block-->",
